messages.message: Hi all, I'm having issues starting `server-nginx`, `ocr-service`, and `redis` . I'm logged in to docker and have called `docker system prune` on my services - getting `exit code: 100`  when I try to start each on docker. Any ideas?
Having the same issues + rabbitmq
can you take a screenshot of your docker env config?
standard config from the onboarding doc but I can increase the number of threads
You've probably already tried this, but my issues ended up being resolved by a restart.
what command did you run?

I just restarted my computer and used the provisioner script

python3 provisioner.py compile lite
It's failing here `apt-get update -y`

Can't seem to find what would have changed to break that. Sorry :disappointed:

Will definitely let you know if something comes to mind.
Could you try building the `redis` docker container manually by cding into `third-party/docker/redis` and run `make build-docker`?
Same with rabbitmq @tony.shi
yep - did that already @Paul H
And it’s erroring out at `apt-get update -y` huh… :thinking_face:
yep :confused:
Could you send a screenshot or a text dump of the error message?
`executor failed running [/bin/sh -c apt remove libunwind-14-dev -y && apt-get update -y]: exit code: 100`

When I run the one liner, this is the error message:
`Error=b"Unable to find image 'instabase/ocr-service:latest' locally
docker: Error response from daemon: pull access denied for instabase/ocr-service, repository does not exist or may require 'docker login': denied: requested access to the resource is denied.
See 'docker run --help'.
make: *** [run-docker] Error 125
"`
although i am logged in to docker
did you restart your laptop and/or docker desktop? https://stackoverflow.com/questions/62625083/apt-and-apt-get-in-dockerfile-returning-error
Yes, restarted both
Do you get the same apt-get error message when you try to manually build ocr-service?
The first error message I get is from manually building, the second message is from the one liner
Ocr-service, redis, and nginx all have the same error messages for both
sanity check: have you turned off zscaler? https://instabase.slack.com/archives/C039JKRCE2H/p1659537903542109
Also, are you on the latest master commit? I recall we had to upgrade our base ubuntu image because we were on a non-LTS version and we were in OOL.
Yeah have the newest image but I can repull master again to try
Are you on an M1 laptop? I was able to rebuild ocr-service and redis locally after running `docker system prune -a`
